76561198062399793,Recommended,226840,32220244,Posted: 6 June,all,noobeman,"(buy with all DLC)Very good 4x game. You recruit heroes, run around with a group of units, kill stuff and capture cities. All units gain experience, levels give them stats and some cool abilities. Cities build units and generate mana to cast spells. Combat is turn-based, happens on a large grid and has quite a lot of depth.PROs:- very involved combat, each battle can end VERY differently depending on what you do;- a lot of different classes (with their own units and spells), leader specialisations (spells) and races (different bonuses and basic units);- long campaign (play on hardest for challenge) - plenty of maps to battle on;- AI is not brilliant, but competent enough.CONs:- the map does not really play a major role in the game, the challenging and engaging gameplay happens pretty much exclusively in battles;- no matter how many turns a battle takes, it's one turn on the strategic map - you can be attacked and killed out of nowhere (you learn to appreciate being able to react to things after playing Civ5).300 hours and I still play this game from time to time. This game clearly has less $$ put into it than something like Civ, but it's really cool - check it out! :)"
