,Recommended,226840,16105402,"Posted: 31 May, 2015",all,Lowen,"What makes Age of Wonders 3 unique compared to other fantasy 4X, and real core of the game are it's turn based tactical battles, there's some serious crunch to them. There are a lot of supporting mechanics, such as spellcasting, flanking, and varying unit types and abilities, but what it all adds up to are tactical battles where you always have interesting choices to make. The battles are fun to watch unfold even after playing for hundreds of hours.The game comes with two fairly long single player campaigns, a random map generator, and an editor that allows you to make your own maps, scenerios, and campaigns.Multiplayer works well, but unfortunately the tactical battles can cause things to grind to a halt. I don't recommend trying to play more than a one on one multiplayer game unless you and your opponent have entire days worth of free time. It's unfortunate considering Endless Legend, another fantasy 4x, integrates tactical battles into the strategic layer nicely and supports multiple tactical battles at once, something Age of Wonders 3 can't manage.AoW3 also has PBEM mode, which I play a lot of. Unfortunately you can't control the player vs player battles in this mode, it's autoresolve only.Overall this is a great game. I also recommend the two expansion DLC that have been released.(edited July 11th 2016: fixed some spelling mistakes)"
76561197981435714,Recommended,226840,31358310,Posted: 25 April,all,Worthless Towel,"First of all I'm a huge fan of Age of Wonders Shadow Magic (Aowsm) and Heroes of might and magic 3 (HoMM).I will compare this game to Aowsm as it should be. It's stays similar to HoMM, but the the bar is still a bit nearer 4X than HoMM series, but it's NOT a 4X as people may intend: This is not a game of diplomacy, of intrigue, of commerce, of research, of politics and population. Not at ALL. It is actually a 2X: Expansion and extermination as HoMM is (the only difference being that in AoW you can build cities and roads and you select which spell/specialisation you want to have next, but that's it): Fund another player? Crush him. Period. If you get this right, you won't be be disappointed expecting a ""Civilization"" style game: Get Endless Legend instead.Let's dig in the core. At first sight, you have the impression the game is a dumbed down version of Aowsm:- less races- only surface/undergrounds- less spells- no more quest for the gods (this one is really pity...).You sacrifice this to have the choice of a race + class. And after some hours you realize the game is much better AowSm. Let's be honest AowSm you ended spawning only Karaghs and Death Angels. All other units are useless in comparison with those ones. In Aow3 endgame troops are not overpowered compared to the rest of the units. As such you end up with more diversified armies, like in HoMM. You will build armies well balanced with units from your race and class. Gameplay will differ a lot depending on the combo race/class you selected and it makes the battles much more strategic than AoWSM.It's according to me the best Heros of might and magic style game ever with HoMM3. If you like this kind of game, this one is a must have."
