76561198006647933,Recommended,226840,9828961,"Posted: 15 April, 2014",all,Low_K,"EDIT 23-11-2016 - This game still stands the test of time, if you still haven't bought it; Do it now!EDIT 17-04-2015 - With the new Eternal Lords expansion in combination with the free 1.5 patch, this game is even better than it was originally.Twelve years we waited for the successor of the excellent Shadow Magic (also available on Steam). And is it worth it? Hell yes!The graphics, soundtrack and (re)playability are excellent!As the Devs are a small company from Holland, and independent publishers, they actively browse and reply on the official forums, making notes of bugs (although there are very few bugs at release) and planning on fixing them in future patches. The same is regarding balancing issues. They are very actively gathering balancing suggestions and also implementing them thorugh patches. They are very close to the community and that is something most software companies can learn from. Regular patches are already released and more are in the pipeline.The game itself comes with an editor, so you can make your own maps/campaigns. Furthermore single-player options are two campaigns, about 8 scenarios and, the icing on the cake, a Random Map Generator. This generator makes very good maps with realistic landmasses. Maps can be selected for small to extra large size and 2-8 players.There is also a multiplayer mode which supports Hotseat (players take turns on the same computer), LAN (need to make contact with official servers first, after that it's offline), VPN (in beta patch at the time of writing) and normal multiplayer games through the internet.I already netted 165 hours in the game, which was released just 16 days ago (at the time of writing) and I just cannot stop playing! This game is highly recommended, not only for gameplay purposes, but also to support the independent developer!"
