,Recommended,226840,9751627,"Posted: 6 April, 2014",all,Sirge,"****Edit on Feb 2015****Purchased and played Golden Realm DLC...ExcellentPro 's-3 part Campaign with storyboard and voice acting, extra gametypes, leaders, units, etc.-Game seems much more balanced and only crashed once on a custom scenario.Con's-I use to be able to host internet games but now you get a connectivity rating and if it is poor you are   not allowed to host game although you can still join them.  (Nothing in my hardware setup has changed, so one of the later game patches must have implemented this.)-though they have done balancing to the game, I still found myself having to reload ingame saves while playing on the easiest skill level.In all I'm moving my rating up to a 9.April 7 2014My review for the 4x, fantasy genre, strategy game called Age of Wonders III.   I had high hopes for this title, as these types of games seem to be few and far between, especially when it come to the game raising the bar and setting a standard for its genre.  I wasn't disappointed at all.  Lets break it down:Graphics: 8Graphics had lots of detail, varied terrain types and meshes that blended well.Music/Sound Effects/Voice acting 8.5Had a great musical score, character acting was top notch, sound effects and environmentals were good too.Controls 8Controls are actually good.  Small issue with some poorly placed, floating info boxes that interfere with selection choices for hero skills.Gamplay 8This could have been so much higher.The good part is content: 2 campaigns, each with 2 different endings.  I have put about 50 hours into the first campaign finishing off both endings.  With still another campaign left, it seems there is alot of content to keep you immersed.  The game also features a multiplayer/co op multiplay option (and it aint ""hotseat"").  You can now finally battle it out, with or against your friends, in a 4x game turnbased strategy game.The bad part is there are some issues.  I started the campaign on normal difficulty and after two or three maps I had to change the setting to easy.  On easy settings it got just as difficult and impossible to complete the last 2 maps without dying a couple dozen times and having to reload the game.  Multiplayer also has issue, infrequent game hangs, and the more frequent friend dropped from game issue.  However, the game allows you to continue with an ai friend or save the game and reload and have your friend rejoin.  Nothing gamebreaking, just a minor annoyance.Overall 8Final thoughtsTriumph Studio was very attentive and  helpful with any issues on launch day.  There are obvious issues that they have noted and promised a quick patch for.  I take it as a good sign if they start pumping out patches before DLC for their game.  There are also gamers who feel the game lacks customization of units or this and that.  I personally feel we have been flooded with sandbox type games, and it has become an expectation that we should be able to create our own game, with the game you give us.  You can create your own custom hero and there is a map maker/editor I have yet to mess with.  With all this to consider, the game doesn't lack, but as any game, can always be improved upon.  Let Triumph get on with the bug fixing, and be patient for the additional content that they promise to work on and deliver.  The game is complete as is and will most likely go down in history as a ""classic""."
