,Recommended,226840,9759400,"Posted: 7 April, 2014",all,MittenMarauder,"For those familiar with the Age of Wonders series, this game is definitely worth playing. The game will immediately feel familiar, while new game mechanics do not feel forced in. Overall, each race still plays like their predecessors, but each leader type will put a twist on your force composition.If you are new to Age of Wonders, this is a Turn Based Strategy game that is based on a series that has been around for some time. Age of Wonders III is similar (but superior) to games like Disciples, and Heroes of Might and Magic. Other similar titles would include Warlock, and Fallen Enchantress. The basics of it are you build an army, learn new spells, and march your gathered army to victory. On the main map, you can cast spells to help you and your allies or hinder your foes. You can explore the map for powerful items to equip your leader and heroes with. When you fight another army you switch to a tactical battle mode. Here, you will command your troops individually, and you are also able to cast magic to aid them.This is not a fast paced game, and larger maps can take a long time to finish. There are some minor issues, such as AI Diplomacy being touchy, however this game excels at Multiplayer as its previous iterations have. The campaign allows you to play both sides of the main conflict, and the achievements allude to 2 endings per side."
