,Recommended,226840,23983394,"Posted: 1 July, 2016",all,<™[-=> Cookiez <=-]™>,"Lovely game. I enjoyed the tutorial immensely. This is a hybrid of Heroes of Might and Magic and Civilization, 2 games that I also enjoy. I prefer the textured map of Heroes of Might and Magic rather than the flat map system of Civilizations. Being able to see the rivers, mountains, streams and the underground make for a much more interesting game.My current feeling is that as 4X games go, Age of Wonders, Endless Legends and Civilizations are currently at the top 3 of my list. Heroes of Might and Magic, Sins of the Solar Empire, TW:Warhammer and Fallen Enchantress are somewhere below.PROS1. The Zoomed In Combat SystemI love this. Combat is based on an Action Point system and is slightly better compared to similar combat systems from 4X games like Endless Legends. You have elevation, terrain, range and spells and even strategic positioning. E.g. If you were to attack an enemy Hero with 2 armies on the left and right flank, the armies will appear on the right and left flank of the enemy as well.2. Feedback ButtonI love the consideration that the developers put in for their players. While I'm sure that the developers aren't able to attend to all feedback, it is a good idea for players to give their feedback. Also, if I ever need to report bugs, this makes it easy to do. Alternatively, F12 works as well.3. Textured Map vs Flat MapYou get to see details versus a plain flat map. Zooming out gives you a Strategic View.4. Lore and ThemeI love the Dreadnought.5. Wall ClimbingVery nice. I like the climbing of walls. It's something that's not in Civilizations or Heroes, not that it's very useful. I'm guessing Total War has had a small impact here?6. Scout CreaturesPrety useful. However, I hate having to summon them. I would prefer an auto-summon familiar.7. Spells instead of TechnologyNot bad. It's thematically more interesting.8. Multiple heroes in CombatLove it, although I am unsure if hero bonuses stack on troops.9. Clearing Underground TerrainI like this strategic element of using the builders to clear soft underground rocks to unlock hidden paths.10. Stacking 6 Units in 1 HexYou have no idea how useful this is compared to Civilization 5's 1 unit per hex.11. Cat and Mouse GamesWhy drag the game out in Cat and Mouse combat? Worse still, add disembarkment.12. Choosing the Main HeroWhy do I have to use Sundren when I have all the other heroes to choose from? Why am I forced to make every single city High Elf?CONS1. Unintuitive ClickingNo auto-pickup. You have to pick it up on your own with a left click and then place it in your inventory. Why can't you just auto-pick it up if you have inventory space?2. RegistrationPain in the♥♥♥♥♥ I understand that you need to use it to link with GOG and Steam though. Please use my Steam account instead.3. Equipping itemsWhy is the bow in your inventory and not held in your hand? Do you go into combat with your weapon stashed in your bag?4. Cliche RacesGoblins, Elves, Orcs, Humans, Dwarves? How much Tolkien do you want to repeat?5. No Parallel BuildsYou can only ever build 1 thing at anytime. Why can't you make an upgrade that builds 2 things at once? E.g. 2 infantry will pop up in a single turn.6. Spellcasting in CombatIf I'm right, only 1 spell can be used per round. Having 2 heroes that can cast spells is redundant. I may have to double-check on this.7. Tedious Strategic SpellsYou have to upgrade you mana nodes manually with a spell. It is useful but tedious.8. Generic Race-Class BuilderGoblin Druid, Orc Druid, Human Druid, Draconian Druid. It destroys the special quality of uniqueness when you have the same units and spells but with a different racial name.9. Relearning Research Skills in CampaginWHY? There is no need to the do it over and over again. This is a campaign. It makes no sense to forget the spells. Just do it like Heroes of Might and Magic and limit the level cap. E.g. You can only research up to level 3 spells at stage 1 of the campaign. Less clutter and confusion.10. Casting Strategic SpellsOMG... This is such a chore. You have to wait a minimum of 1 turn before you can cast a strategic spell and some of them are meant for builders. E.g. Create Air Node. WTF is this? Why do you need to cast? You copied the wrong things.11. Entering and Exiting UndergroundYou have to move onto the entrance, double left click to select the entrance and then press enter. It's so tedious.12. Building BridgesWTF? Only on 1 Hex water tiles? Why 1 tile? Why can't you just build a long straight bridge that connects to another island. This links to disembarkment.NEUTRAL1. Expanding your Territory with BuildersNot bad, but not perfect. Instead of using builders for roads and industrial upgrades, you build settlements that increase your city's domain. Compared to buying tiles with culture, it's much better. However, the builders need to be given instructions, otherwise they are pieces of junk. If you don't expand, it stands around doing nothing. Builders are really tedious to use as they are non-military but they still hog your unit selection. You can't automate them to build roads or clear trees."
