76561198024475280,Recommended,226840,33053471,Posted: 30 June,all,Hector of Troy,"The best turn based combat system I've seen so far.Combat flows naturally here. Even in crowded sieges, the mechanics keep it simple, organized, practical and fun. Classes and races genuinely differ from each other, and one set of troops and abilities may not be as effective against different foes.It is also worth mentioning the vast amount of information and tooltips displayed everywhere. Features are absolutely transparent. It is even possible to plan ahead according to the knowledge of the number of tiles an opponent may move in the next turn.The sheer amount of customization is amazing as well. After a few playthroughs, you will be able to play exactly how you want Age of Wonders 3 to be like.The campaign mechanics are also elegant and fascinating. Highly recommended.My only criticism is that I believe I would have enjoyed this sequel even more if the developers had chosen to make it a slow paced empire management game instead of a  fast war conquest one. In fact, there are already mechanics in place that I believe could make this transition possible. Only a few tweaks here and there, and perhaps some necessary new implementations, would probably suffice.Triumph Studio should seriously consider making a game like that. They definitely have the skills to come up with a great empire management strategy title."
