,Recommended,226840,25303060,"Posted: 2 September, 2016",all,uuneter,"This was my first Age of Wonders game. I've played tons of HoMM up to 3, but no Civ or any other 4x games. Overall I like the game and recommend it. It took me five restarts of the first campaign before I ""got"" it, so you might need to be patient.The story is indepth, if you enjoy that (admittedly I started skipping it a few missions in - just wanted to play). The graphics are great. So far I've made it through most of the Elven campaign. You get to play several different heroes. Each one has many different skills to choose. You'll find loot along the way that you equip on your heroes. There are several different quests for each map, some optional.There's lots of exploring, including underground. Lots of fighting as well. The battles are hex based, similar to tabletop games. One thing you'll learn is you'll want at least two armies when attacking. The battles are strategic - obstacles that cause line of sight penalties, flanking, hero spells, siege attacks if someone is in a city, support-group spells and abilites, etc.On the postive, I enjoy exploring the map and battling, although I auto battle a lot because it's quicker. The graphics are nice. I like the loot you pick up. As someone who's never played an AoW game before, I do find the AI challenging, even on Easy. If the AI has an advantage, it will attack your army. Any time you leave a city undefended, the AI will take it. And it seems very smart in the battles; it doesn't make dumb moves.For the negatives, I find the game repetitive. I build up my cities pretty much identical each map. So far all of the maps have just been ""Defeat the other players."" Manual battles can be lengthy which makes it tough if you have limited playing time. There is such an advantage to being in a city for a fight that you can trap the AI in a city as you buildup other armies to attack. I've run into this repeatedly - having to track down ""turtled"" enemy heroes in cities and build up large enough armies to win.There are some negatives for me, but I do still enjoy playing the game. I'm almost finished with the Elven campaign and hoping the other campaign offers more than just ""Defeat all enemies"" every map."
