76561197971745805,Recommended,226840,24361849,"Posted: 16 July, 2016",all,RoflMan,"Very good game with alot of content. Especially the random maps are good (with lots of sliders to tune it to your liking incase you would want that), but the campaigns are also decent and there are loose scenario maps. Keep in mind though that while this is tagged as a 4x game, the combat part (turn based) is dominant and leveling up your hero and units is very important too. In short combat and exploration are really important.I highly recommend buying the game with the 2 expansions Golden Realm and Eternal Lords. Not only are new classes, races and specialisations added, some addional gameplay features are added and new ways to win.+ lots of possible combinations by picking your race and your class and spell specialisations. E.g. a sorcerer that summons whole armies, or a necro that has undead armies, or a dreadnought that has many machines.+ be dark (plunder villages and kill of whole races), gray or good (e.g. helping villages with quests so they will join your empire or as vassals), based on actions and not race. Do whatever you like. Also several decisions in the storyline that you can make.+ rich maps filled neutral ctities, hideouts, dungeons, recources, neutral places that give bonuses to nearby cities, tavern to hire units, etc. etc.  Lots of places to level up and gain loot. Also secundary quests.+ The random map generator is one of the best I have ever seen.+ lots of units and quite a bit of buildings and upgrades for villages/cities.+ the bigger your empire with a race and the longer you have it, the more race bonuses you will get (you pick between upgrades).+ all units can rank up which give them interesting abilities and add lots of tactics. With your leader and heroes you can pick between quite a bit upgrades/abilities per level up.+ lots of items, spells and abilities.+ less RNG than similar games.+ good backlore.+ moddable and there are mods for it.-/+ can be difficult to turtle or forward base defending tactics, though with some classes and races its more viable.- a map can get tough when you have a bad start (e.g. you lose some starting units or are to slow with leveling them).- still some annoying RNG, but luckily not so much.- minor point: while campaings are decent, I feel that the story could have been more epic. Can't really put my finger on it though, since the backlore (especially with AoW 1 and 2) is pretty expansive.My score: 9. Pro's to the developers for having patched this game many times."
