,Recommended,226840,35007055,Posted: 16 September,all,GarrickWinter,"This is one of my favourite 4X games of this generation (alongside Endless Legend). I love the simplicity of it - conquer cities, build improvements, make more stuff and throw it at your enemies again. Diplomacy and economics are shallow, but they're all they need to be (no upkeep on buildings is a godsend for my sanity) - the focus is really on warfare, with a bewildering array of units and factions and spells and bonuses that can tip things one way or the other.I particularly like how your faction isn't just a race, but a combinaton of your race and your leader. So all Elves share things in common, and all Rogues share things in common, but playing as an Elf Rogue is different to both an Orc Rogue and an Elf Cleric, for example. Races and leaders each contribute their own units and bonuses and so forth, and learning how to use your favourites and counter unusual combinations is great fun. This extra dimension makes for a ton of variety and flavour.Everything looks great and the music is pretty good, and the tactical battles where you're winning by the skin of your teeth really shine. Definitely worth getting the two campaign DLCs too, Golden Realms and Eternal Lords."
