76561198154269385,Recommended,226840,31100570,Posted: 12 April,all,Spicy Bagels,"Okay so let's get on with a short review.MAP:The map is basically like Civ, it's a hexagon based map where each army or character has a certain move limit which is affected by the terrain type before having to end your turn to be able to move again on your next go. There are all sorts of treasures and dungeons, some with high difficulty and high rewards, located all over the map and other resource or unit providing structures. The map also has different biomes, which your race will benefit or receive negative attributes from depending on which race you choose. For example, High Elves will benefit greatly in battles if they're fighting in Forest-temperate terrain types, but receive negative effects from fighting on a frozen landscape for example. This varies depending on which race you choose.COMBAT:Okay, so combat is a little more develloped than Civ, it's a turn-based, tiled space movement system which takes place on a different map than the campaign one. Terrain and line of sight also affect ranged units an so on. The only thing I dislike about combat is that it's relatively small-scale, even if you combine 3 armies, the battles still feel small which I personally dislike being a big Total War fan. Still the combat is good and so is unit variation and having a good strategy can decide whether you win or loose a battle.GAMEPLAY:So, you choose a race and then your faction leader has a class, for example, druid, necromancer (dlc), mage, rogue, engineer and each have their own benefits and weaknesses, as well as unique units, spells and abilities. The aim of the game is to basically wipe-out your enemies for a total victory or an allied victory. There are also different game types available to choose from so replayability is pretty decent. You can also find loot to upgrade your faction leader and generals as well as level them up and choose new skills and abilities for them.VERDICT:I highly recommend this game to all turn-based strategy fans, especially those who enjoy the fantasy genre.8/10"
