76561197971907582,Recommended,226840,12194254,"Posted: 22 September, 2014",all,ThatWhichThinks,"Short Version: The game looks gorgeous, has tons of replayability with a solid battle AI, and some of the most fun tactial battles of any game I can think of.  If you want fantasy battles look no further.Longer Version: A lot of people compare this game to Fallen Enchantress or Civ, and I think that comparison does very little justice to any of the games involved.  All three games are 4X games in that you can explore, exploit, expand, and exterminate enemies, but have very different focuses.  In general, Civilization games thrive on the first three ""x""s but have awful, boring warfare.  Fallen Enchantress is well-rounded, with decent battles and interesting RPG mechanics, but ultimately leaves a lot of the exploitation to be desired.  AoW 3 would be at the extreme opposite Civ: the battles are great, and, nominally, so are the other x's, but there is very little to do with any resource except use it to eXterminate.  The good news is that battles are a lot of fun with dozens of well-balanced, interesting units and lots of great spells."
,Recommended,226840,12204457,"Posted: 23 September, 2014",all,Dimuyen,"A great fantasy strategy gameAlthough I think this game doesn't fully capture the ""wonders"" part of the old Age of Wonders it's a great addition to the modern fantasy strategy genre. This is primarily a quibble on the look of the game based on versions 1 & 2. Particularly in the strategic map, I feel that the new version lacks on a certain visual feedback that the old ones had that made them look more woundrous and magical than the new version does. You may not agree with me on this, and that's fine, it really doesn't affect the gameplay.The hero creation is interesting and varied, and the hero that leads your army has a significant impact on gameplay as the units/spells available vary depending on your choices. There are interesting items you can get, including a variety of mounts. I still wish this part was a bit more fleshed out, but it's still enough to make that part of the game interesting.Large campaign maps take forever and a day to complete, which sounds great but I still have yet to finish one.I've spent very little time in the game's campaign, I usually just play random maps."
