76561197999356538,Recommended,226840,9704322,"Posted: 2 April, 2014",all,MattStriker,"I'll start with the good news: this really is a worthy successor to the earlier parts of the series, and I definitely recommend it to any fan of turn-based strategy games.That said, it does have a few flaws that need to be addressed.- The alignment system...doesn't work. There's nopenaltyto playing the good guy, so you'll pretty much always gravitate towards a Pure Good alignment unless you make a deliberate effort to be evil, and since therearedistinct penalties for playing the bad guy you end up gimping yourself in the progress.- While the move to 3D certainly improved animation quality, some models (especially flying creatures) are just plain hideous to look at. I have absolutelynoidea what they were trying to achieve with the gryphon, for example :P.- The loss of many staple races is a bit of a pain, although the new class-based units do help to put some of the variety back in.- Speaking of that, some things about the race/class system aren't exactly explained very well. Class units of different races do have noticably different stats, which is something you're left to find out for yourself (hint: elves, as usual, doverywell with any kind of ranged attack).- And finally, there's a certain amount of interface clunkiness going on. No major showstoppers, but a lot of minor things that'll get a little annoying over time.So...what makes this worth buying despite the flaws I just outlined?- A solid TBS experience with RPG elements.- A fun, if somewhat cliché'd setting.- Amazing music.- Elven musketeers.- The classes really do offer vastly different playstyles. If you try the approach you won with as a Warlord with an Archdruid character, you will probably fail pretty hard.- Character traits make ahugedifference in playstyle as well.- Goblin angels.- Random map generator with good fine-tuning options provides long-term replayability.- The series' trademark sense of humor is still around and going strong, particularly in the unit descriptions.All in all, a very solid game despite some flaws, and probably the best of its kind out right now."
