,Recommended,226840,18319949,"Posted: 3 October, 2015",all,Warboys,"TLDR: 7.5/10It's very good but there are so many things that drive me mad that I can't honestly say it's a classicAge of Wonders is basically what Heroes of Might & Magic should have become after the countless crapfest sequels that didn't try anything new. The game has a wonderful tactical combat system that puts most regular tactical combat games to shame, it's really exciting and there are so many cool abilities and spells to use. Overall there's a lot of content (I'm just reviewing the vanilla game) and plenty of variety for a good 1-2 playthroughs of each Class.The downsides? Well like most 4X style games, it doesn't handle scale well. The economy is super simple and isn't the focus of the game (unlike Civ V for example), so it falls into the trap of ""I don't ♥♥♥♥ing care about these 6 cities I've built"". I know I should care, and I need to care in the late game... it's just too much tedious management with very little impact on your game as a whole, especially compared to the early game. Likewise for armies. You start with 1x 6-unit army, including your hero, and have nice little skirmishes. Then you get Hero after Hero with army after army and before you know it you've got 10 armies you have to manage and fight with. It's just too much and I find the turns take so long and the decisions become so diluted down that I quit most games once I've killed my main rival. It's a pain to finish an Age of Wonders game.Minor gripes;  Bone Dragon independent parties flying around from outside the fog of war and destroying your entire army isn't fun. It spams you with 'This hero wants to join' every ♥♥♥♥ing turn, which is soooo god damn time consuming over the course of a 100-200 turn game. Furthermore, the extra heroes you get are very sub-standard and some, like the Dreadnaught, are basically useless as you lack the Class buildings for your cities to get any of the units that Hero would need. Auto-Combat is sometimes a little ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥t, killing dudes that obviously wouldn't have died if you'd done manual combat... then again, the combat does take so long that you find yourself using Auto for most situations that aren't an 18vs18 city siege.Tiny gripes which might be my fault for sucking? I find the whole economy and tech side of the game a little shallow. It seems that for most classes it's all about just getting as many Shadow Stalkers or Eldrich Horrors as you possibly can, removing any unit diversity and relegating most units to the 'useless leagues'. The game does do a good job of keeping diversity high into the mid-game, but end-game it's just dull. Also that Call of the Wild spell that summons 3 beasts every ♥♥♥♥ing round is so stupidly good, ♥♥♥♥ dat♥♥♥♥♥♥"
