,Recommended,226840,9838144,"Posted: 16 April, 2014",all,Kernyx,"The game is in general well developed.It's not a clone of any other game, it's got its own long history and deserves its place in the genre of 4X games.While there might be some performance issues and some little flaws here and there, the issues are easily solved by turning off anti-aliasing (which is not really important in a 4X game) and the flaws are already being fixed.The developer is currently actively patching the game and already fixed a lot of issues and added a couple features.The AI might not be able to trick the player but it works well and there are a lot of options to interact with the player.The graphics look good, the controls are pretty good.Since it is a turn based game that consumes a lot of CPU performance you should know that there are two types of turn systems.One is where all can move at the same time. This reduces your waiting time but while the AI moves you have to wait till your clicks are registered.The other is where each player has their own turn. That increases your waiting time, but while its your turn, you can click around without delays.The story catches up on the events of the previous titles and sounds interesting, we might see an add-on for this game.While the story campaign falls a little short, the random map generator, world editor, scenario mode and multiplayer mode allow you to experience new maps and new opponents every time you play.I believe AoW3 is a well made sequel."
