76561197991088969,Recommended,226840,15279893,"Posted: 9 April, 2015",all,Sethfcm,"I should have reviewed this game long ago.Age of Wonders 3 is an amazing fantasy turn based 4x with rpg elements, and a fantastic array of choices, customization and tactical options.I would sit here and list them all, but I will condense it to afew points.Have you ever played a 4x and wanted to actually be on the battlefield? To have a presence? In AoW 3 you can, as a sovereign you can fight on the battlefield (and revive if killed too) gain levels, and lead a glorious army, or have your heroes do it for you (or fight alongside them)Have you ever wanted to be able to both play a nice, friendly, intercultural hero of the people? Or be the devious evil genociding brutal wizard lord? Both are viable strategies, and have their strengths and weaknesses especially with all the new updates related to alignment, and racial approval/happiness.Do you itch for a game with a varied class selection of rather different yet equal classes? From the ttrategy, tactics, and military might of the warlord, and the sneaky cunning of the rogue to the vast arcane power of the wizard and religious/moral power of the theocrat (and several other classes, alongside the necromancer soon to be released) you have access to a vast array of balanced, interesting, and flavorful classes.Balance is both already good, and improving all the time as the developers follow the approach of Adding content, and adding power rather than simply cutting content, and nerfing to improve balance, orks not strong enough? We aughta give them a new unit option, and a damage buff, not nerf everyone else. It's wonderful, and so very productive.All in all do I feel like I got my money's worth with this purchase? I very much do, I was worried after years without a new game that this game would fail to live up to the nostalgia of AoW Shadow Magic, instead it actually improved upon it's predecessor, and captured my attentions all over again.