erences in HOW the different civilizations will approach destroying you.  In AoW II it's like being swarmed by a hoard of really angry bees.  Why are they attacking you?  No ♥♥♥♥ing reason at all... they just ARE.So that's that.  Would this game get a thumbs up if it were MORE interesting in a lot of it's aspects than just ""enough"" depth of customization or just ""enough"" of 4x or if it's different civilizations weren't exactly the same just named differently?  Yes.  And I feel like the makers of this game knew they were making a game that was, in fact, only just ""enough""... that's why it's $40 rather than $50 or $60.  In the end it's a shallow and pretty game with some decent music that costs too much.  Buy it when it's on sale."
