,Recommended,226840,13216748,"Posted: 3 December, 2014",all,twitch.tv/go8bitmaster,"I like 4x. I do. It's a great genre for fans of strategy. After playing hours upon hours of civ 4,  a few of the total war games, warlock 2,  civ 5, then finally beyond earth, I started to get a bit bored on basic science and diplomatic based victories because I just didn't like combat in civ. I picked up Age of Wonders 3 during the past sale, and I'm really enjoying myself. Compared to civ, elements like the way tech and buildings worked took a bit to get used to, but i'm really starting to fall in love with the game. It combines the grand 4x strategy of civ, with a much better combat system similar to what you would see in a hex based strategy game like might and magic, and I feel the fusion was extremely well done. I'm doing something I haven't done in a strategy game like this in a long time, and that is seek out combat. I love the feeling of flanking opponents for massive damage, just to realize I left a commander unguarded and having to wait a few turns before it respawns, and having to build up armies again. I'm still in the middle of my first game, but I can forsee many more in my future, and would recommend this to my civ loving friends out there, especially if you're getting sick of boring combat. 9/10"
