,Recommended,226840,9758941,"Posted: 7 April, 2014",all,Zxoronto,"So far, this game is living up to they hype.  Having a chance to play every race and class, there seem to be perhaps the need for a few minor balancing issues.  Most of the main concerns are already underway in future patch releases.  Minor bugs exist, but nothing game-breaking from what I have seen.  The ONLY downside so far is the inability to connect directly to play with a friend.  Fiddling with the router/port forwarding, etc may be necessary to play across their servers in multiplayer.This game gives more versatility than any of the previous games with the class/race system.  It stays simplified and is quick to pick up if having played previous games.  One new difference is the DOMAIN feature.  It sure saves from scrambling for nodes!For those who have not played any of the previous games in this series, it is a turn-based tactical game.  Multiplayer tends to be slower than single, but with customizable terrains to add to the random map generating, options are endless!"
