76561198039929207,Recommended,226840,15749935,"Posted: 8 May, 2015",all,whathappenus,"I almost didn't got this game because many people here say that it is just a Civilization clone. I love Civ but I was not going to play another Civ mod. But I saw it on sale and decided to get it. So to get this out of the way: this is not a Civ mod. It doesn't feel like a Civ game. The emphasis here is combat not building civilizations. The main point of the game is that you have M different races for your heroes and N different classes, giving you an NxM possible ways to build your heroes. They are very different from one another depending of your race and class. Playing a rogue/gnome plays vastly different than a dreadnought/dwarf, just to give an example. This gives the game  a vast replay value.Each hero  carries an army of 5 units (six including the hero which is also a unit in battle). Battles can be fought with up to 6 armies. These are fought on battlefields that open up like in Heroes of Might and Magic. Battlefields can be a city and if you attack it many armies surrounding the city, the battlefield will show the town perhaps surrounded by walls and the armies surrounding the city in all directions. Battlefields can be in open spaces with obstacles in between. This is really cool and makes battles complex affairs.Outside of the battle you control cities, build new cities, and build/research armies and upgrades. Positioning your heroes prior to the battle is an interesting strategic element. You might start approaching a city trying to surrounded it only to see an enemy hero attack one of your armies that might have come to close to the city. So you might loose that army and weaken your forces to take the city.Plus points:+ Not a Civ clone. This is a different turn-based game+ Emphasis on combat; not so much in empire management+ Strong RPG elements; many different classes and units that makes you want to play again with different combinations+ Many cool items and gear for your heroes can be found scattered in the map+ lengthy campaign and randomly generated scenarios+ Difficulty levels so you can start easy or make it challengingMinus points:- Graphic/isometric view is good but nothing to call home about- Storyline in the first campaign (haven’t tried the second one) is told by a long story but it is not really interesting. Not sure why TBS games don’t come with cutscenes and interesting stories like some RTS gamesScore: 9/10 for combat gameplay and strong RPG."
