76561198034403688,Recommended,226840,16507310,"Posted: 18 June, 2015",all,snigglyfoo,"Great fantasy strategy game got even better with patchesRecent patches (June 2015) really improved the gameplay. There are too many changes to list, but you might want to check it out if played the initial game version but not recently.One paragraph description of AoWTo me, AoWIII is the best of the fantasy strategy genre which includes: Might & Magic, King's Bounty, Warlock, King Arthur, Eador, etc. Gameplay is centered around managing a few heroes which gain strength by leveling, research, and acquiring items. Your heroes can also lead armies and capture cities. Cities allow you to build more units and improve resources. Combat is turn-based on a hex map against a challenging AI. Hero items and experience persist between campaign missions which take awhile to finish.If you liked the previous AoWs, this is a great sequel, similar to what Civ5 is to Civ4. Everything gets better."
