,Recommended,226840,13149346,"Posted: 29 November, 2014",all,PnzrNorm,"For all the hex-grid 4X lovers out there, this game is for you.Think of Civilization 5 with a fantasy theme but add RPG stats and skills to your civ's leader, then they become a controllable hero unit on the map, AND units can stack into armies.THEN whenever you fight in combat, zoom in to an expanded version of the hex on the map, and its a-whole-nother hex grid to fight over complete with varying terrain, elevation, climate, and occasionally besieging a city or fort's walls!And then there's the massive depth to each unit. Not just the heroes, but each individual military unit will have their own RPG-style stats with strengths and weaknesses and even crazier promotions than you could possibly imagine (my favorite so far is getting a flying, flame-breathing dragon mount for my leader and handing the horse off to another general)In the war of 4X, I've seen a lot of games rise to the occasion, and a lot more of them fall flat but this one takes the cake."
