76561198073266627,Not Recommended,226840,17002440,"Posted: 11 July, 2015",all,Tzarkon,"First I'd like to say I don't totally hate this game. There are aspects that are done well and are enjoyable. The graphics are very nice. The battles are well done. Having the ability to decide whether battles are AI controlled or manual is nice. The options for kinds of leaders are well done.That having been said there are several aspects of the game that are deal breakers for me. First, having to connect to the AOW servers even to play a LAN game is annoying. Not having an IP connection option unless through a VPN is more than annoying. The lack of this feature that we use in many other games makes the game feel unfinished at best.It's obvious that the AOW servers do not really have the bandwidth to accomodate the numbers of players that they have. Of the three players I normally play with I have the middle connection to the internet. I have been completely unable to get a speed adequate to host a game. Weirdly, the player in our group with the fastest connection also can not get a connection fast enough to host. However, our player with the slowest connection has been able to, though it fades in and out. Since we play other games that have similar connection requirements and we are all able to host, it is clearly a problem with the bandwidth at AOW. Not being able to host makes the game unplayable.We started playing as allies vrs AI players. The game taking us into the battles of the other players from whatever we're doing and focing us to watch the battle rather than allowing us to continue our turns in a simultaneous turn based interface is a very poor programming choice. That alone makes the game frustrating enough and actually makes it unplayable for the duration of the battle.At this point, several of us are playing through our first game. I can't wait to finish the game and go back to playing another simultaneous turn based game. I'd really like to like this game, but without a direct IP connect, inadequate bandwidth at the AOW server, and forced watching of battles during turns of allies, I won't be back to play again and can't recommend this game to others."
