,Recommended,226840,26148419,"Posted: 21 October, 2016",all,Kydrago,"Just bought this game earlier this week and have been playing it non-stop with a friend of mine. It shares many economic and empire-building mechanics with Civilization 5, but gameplay is much more focused around combat and conquest, and games tend to be shorter (at least thus far). Combat, unlike in Civ, is done on a small-scale tactical level, where the camera essentially zooms in to the individual hex where the units are battling, and both players use their armies and units on a small scale. To me, this is the most significant thing that makes this game enjoyable (along with the leader customization, which had me in tears laughing on day 1). While $30 is a high price, this game certainly feels worth it this far in.TL;DR: Like Civ, except fun."
