,Recommended,226840,14493676,"Posted: 15 February, 2015",all,Anal Mayonaise,"*CAUTION*: I would rate this game 3.5/5 stars.Bottom Line: What this game does, this game does well; but it's what it doesn't do that hurts the most. It's worthwhile for multiplayer, but for singleplayer I'd look elsewhere. My personal recommendation would be Fallen Enchantress Legendary Heroes.This game offers some of the most advanced features found in any 4X game, but at the expense of bread-and-butter features we've all come to love and expect. For example: Every unit has numerous abilities, but you're only allowed to cast up to a certain amount of magic per turn (ie. campaign map turn); this means that you could have hundreds of battles per turn, but end up using magic in only a handful. Personally, I think this is extremely unreasonable and silly. I am not opposed to having a global mana pool (which this game does have), but I think it is much more realistic and enjoyable to have casting units use spells every battle round than just be subject to a global cap. Even a per-battle cap or per-unit-per-battle or per-unit-per-turn cap would have been more reasonable. I understand that this must have been implemented as a way to prevent exploiting battle through repetitive casting, but it would have been better to counterbalance the repeated-casting system rather preventing it from happening in the first place.I also very much miss the ""crowd attack"" feature, in which allies adjacent to the enemy join in on melee attacks, that games such as Fallen Enchantress have.Sure, we might have multi-army battles, but what's the point when the quality of an individual battle when down the toilet?And the campaign maps are so boring! Yeah, the terrain is very well varied, and naval battles aren't terrible (though they aren't great either), but the almost complete and total lack of events, and the very elementary spawning of mobs and acquisition of heroes leaves much to be desired. Contrast, again, to Fallen Enchantress, in which events are varied and frequent, both good and bad, both global and local, and where mobs spawn and respawn as opposed to be eliminated once and for all once they are defeated. Yeah, Fallen Enchantress isn't perfect (the #1 problem: it lacks multiplayer!!! But I still think it is the greatest single-player 4X game of all time, at the time of writing), nor is any 4X game (currently!), but the best way to describe AOW3 in one word is disproportionate. Enjoyable in aspects, and frustratingly deprived in others."
