,Recommended,226840,15569728,"Posted: 26 April, 2015",all,Lotabeer,"This game is amazing. I have probably never enjoyed spending large amounts of time in a non-MMO game before. That being said, I found the introductory experience to be very rocky. If you're a newbie to these games/this genre like I was: play on EASY at least for the first mission. I've sunk just shy of 60 hours into the game so far and I'd say that I might actually understand the basics of intermediate-level play now, which is enough for me to fumble through (and thoroughly enjoy) the game on low difficulty, while constantly learning more. I can see this being a game where you would need hundreds of hours to comprehensively understand it on a high level due (without running into surprises) to the sheer number of variables involved. This may sound daunting but it's actually fantastic on a semi-casual level since it keeps you constantly sucked in with new content and gameplay. I have zero interest in online play and yet this game still feels like it could provide 200+ hours of solid play for me.Only real downside is that, for all it's strides toward modernization, there are still many barriers to accessability in this game that will require research to overcome. With searching and good old guess-and-check, you will come to learn it well, but it's annoying that even with the seemingly comprehensive in-game encyclopedia, there are many nuances of game mechanics that are not very intuitive or easy to master (constrained cities? Flanking criteria in tactical battles?). Old school gamers would call this part of the fun of the game, since you have to learn by being occasionally punished by unknowable rules, but I tend to think this is unacceptable in modern gaming and it just feels pointlessly dated to me.Overall though I dont think I could reccomend this game highly enough and I haven't even dipped a toe into the DLC yet. I got it half off but it's easily worth the full price if you dont feel like waiting for a sale."
