76561198111672496,Recommended,226840,14758581,"Posted: 6 March, 2015",all,matthew.tobin01,"This is a beautiful and quirky game, the setting is lush and exciting. However, the quirkiness can actually be something of a problem. A player is limited to a rather small army, especially at the beginning of the game. This limit does not seem to apply to the computer player, however. Again, this game is designed so that you explore the fascinating landscapes rather than ""hunker down"" at your capital and other cities. The army limits also apply to your cities, so I found myself playing almost a completely defensive game with my armies in my capital and towns, and the immediate ""hex boxes"" encircling those just waiting for massive computer armies to attack me. I'd have liked to see more of the world, but this was almost impossible because I found my explorers ruthlessly hunted down by the computer while at the same time wiping out my capital and cities. Also, you have to generate plenty of resources in your cities to fund and feed your armies, which precluded having armies to even match the size of a computer player. 3 out of 5 Stars."
