,Recommended,226840,15366629,"Posted: 14 April, 2015",all,Endothlyne,This is more of a praise for the developers than a review. There are plenty of those already.  Originally I got this game not long after its release. I played it for a bit but I just couldn't get ino it. Its difficult to pin point exactly why but it just didn't gel with me. After reading about update 1.5 I decided to give the game another shot. I'm glad I did because this time after starting with a new campaign the game has grown on me. They have made a lot of tweaks and improvements since I last played it. It shows some dedication when developers like this try so hard to improve the game. They could have quite easily walked away and abandoned it.I think the initial problem with this game is that there was huge expectation prior to its release given the popularity of the older games. Rather than give up though the developers actually listened to their fan base and kept on making improvements. You don't often see that kind of devotion when the release of a game doesn't quite go to plan.The latest expansion looks great and it could be the one that completely turns this game around. I'm going to wait a while though and continue playing with the original. By then there will be a lot more feedback about eternal lords and I get the feeling it will be mostly positive.If like me you were not completely taken by AOW III on its release I recommend you give it another try as you may be pleasantly surprised.
