76561198031515788,Recommended,226840,14602398,"Posted: 22 February, 2015",all,Amaraktar,"Kind of disappointed after really getting into Shadow Magic a few years ago. This one just isn't as good - the campaigns are nowhere near the great level of story we got in AOW:SM, and while the Wizard classes have been separated out a bit (so you're playing more a style rather than an element), there's a morality system (straight Good / Evil) which makes roleplaying properly pretty difficult. There are the usual mobs guarding each useful resource, but a good Elf killing these independent elves gives you evil points - the same goes for if you're playing Orcs killing independent goblins or trolls guarding a mine - you would get ""Good"" points for doing this.....Doesn't make a whole lot of sense to me, but the main sticking points for me are the campaign story and secondly the zoom-in battles. I realise a lot of people complained that ranged units were a bit OP before, but now you just can't get in a shot in city sieges before climbers and wall-passers are on you!Another smaller not-really-a-problem was that there was a lack of heroes turning up. The levelling system for them seems improved and my few ended up with far too much gear - have more turn up please!6/10 - If you like this kind of 4X exploration / city-building / TBC then I'd buy Shadow Magic instead. Much better."
