,Recommended,226840,13556809,"Posted: 23 December, 2014",all,dwiggs,"A great iteration on a classic series - my favorite of the three by far. The game was pretty solid on release, wandered over into ""excellent"" territory after Golden Realms and the accompanying balance/content patches, and is looking to cross over into ""unbelievable"" with the Necromancer/Frostling expansion coming in early 2015 (new content, well-thought out balance and strategic adjustments, and a unique server-side Play-By-Email variant!)Icing on the cake - the dev team at Triumph is incredible; they've always been very sharp, responsive, and friendly.The one area I'd give this game a lower grade for would be its campaign. While they've tried to fill the campaign with a rich story and interesting events, sometimes the underlying 4X game doesn't mesh so well with the campaign goals, and those maps turn into tight rushes or long slogs. The game truly shines in its individual scenarios and especially in its well-done random map generator, both in SP and MP."
