,Recommended,226840,13666102,"Posted: 28 December, 2014",all,fryhtaning,"As someone who was raised on the Civ and Heroes of Might and Magic series, this game has surprised me with how well it incorporates elements from both.  The overworld is very HoMM-esque, and the combat is much better and more strategic.  The city-building is not as deep as a Civ game, of course, but it punishes you very well if you try to ""complete"" every city with all of the available buildings.  If you sit back and try and build a mega army, without any defenses, you'll get squashed by wave after wave of enemy forces, so you're forced into prioritizing your military cities vs your money/resource-acquiring cities.  The game is gorgeous and the music is great.  I bought this game a month before the Steam sales began and I don't regret one bit the fact that I could have saved another $10-15."
