76561198042102876,Recommended,226840,10766231,"Posted: 24 June, 2014",all,Whiskeyjoel,"A great successor to the original AoW games...and after so many years! When I first heard that the game was going into production, and that the same ORIGINAL TEAM, plus new additions, were working on it...my mind was blown.This, I thought, is fan service done right. And I was not disappointed. The AoW franchise has always been a cult classic in the SRPG genre; hell, they helped CREATE the genre, and with AoW3, they show that they still have the magic. The game itself is beautiful, especially the battlegrounds, the voice acting is superb, combat is deep and highly strategic, and the hero customization is great. This is a fantastic game in every way"
,Recommended,226840,13606227,"Posted: 25 December, 2014",all,SanMan,"I was looking for something reminiscent of Heroes of Might and Magic, King's bounty, and Civ. I found it here. I find it very fun both for the campaign and for local coop play. There is a loyal and dedicated following of players, and they discuss tactics and balancing issues on forums everywhere. There is also a very helpful wiki online. The pace is slow and not for casual gamers.The game has three layers of strategy to it. There is the individual battle tactics level, there is the world map level where you are moving units around, and then there is the economics and logistical level of gameplay. Just because you are strong in one aspect of the game, doesn't mean you will be able to easily overpower others because of it. You can also tailor your characters to match your strengths and weaknesses based upon their abilities.Great game. I recommend it.Update: this remains one of the few games that I keep coming back to. This game is full of variety and depth. The artwork is beautiful. The strategy and tactics vary tremendously and you can find a hundred different ways to combine races, classes, and schools of magic. These combinations also play a role in what kind of special skills or abilities your units have. There are different kinds of games to play, with many customizable options."
