76561198053073822,Recommended,226840,16819901,"Posted: 30 June, 2015",all,PaleBlueDot,"I considered writing this review paying special attention to the differences between this and age of wonders 1 (I never played the others in the series, sad to say) but I decided against that. If you are a returning fan and you somehow haven't made up your mind about this game two years after it came out, just buy the game, you'll like it, even though it's very, very different. Now, for the uninitiated:+The factions, magic spheres, and all seem fairly balanced. Some combinations are better than others but nothing feels like a trap, although I've never felt it was worth it to take the explorer trait, or partisan. Some spells and upgrades in the air tree nombo with each other, imo. The DLC makes the theocrat feel a lot better to play by adding necromancers, who have some advantages over other players but tend to get hurt pretty bad by spirit damage. The necromancer, however, does have a variety of options to cope with this, so it's not a ""I got beat before the game began"" situation.+The treasure site system results in the game feeling similar to Heroes of Might and Magic in some ways. I don't think it's a problem.+The artstyle is charming, even though wyverns look pretty derpy.+Goblins are cute, in a muppet way. My friends tell me that I am dead wrong about this.+Music is good.+There is an alignment system based on your behavior. Playing like a hippie is Good, and being a murderous tyrant is Evil. It feels pretty natural.+Make custom characters and play as your waifu, unless you want a red haired elf. Because elves all have pink hair.+Build your own customized magic items+Ride on wyverns, wolves, giant spiders and diseased pigs.+Summon flying squid monsters that breathe electricity.-in single player your first and highest priority is to hunt down all the lairs that spawn monsters, from rogue camps that spawn scoundrels to graveyards that spawn zombie dragons and giants. You must prioritize this because the AI factions won't do it, and if you let those lairs fester they WILL capture cities from you. It takes up time I would maybe rather spend fighting other players or something.-It gets pretty silly sometimes, especially if you read the lore. A lizard tied to a stick is a legendary usable item and the unicorn description makes references to My Little Pony and that stupid robot unicorn game.-Alignment doesn't really help with anything but diplomacy unless you have the DLC.TL;DR: This is a clever blend of RPG and 4x in which you can be a goblin who rides a giant vampire spider and dual-wields a musket and a shotgun."
