76561198030545819,Not Recommended,226840,23518962,"Posted: 12 June, 2016",all,p9000,"This review of for Age of Wonders III on OS X.This game seems extremely interesting and full of promise.  I played the original Age of Wonders years ago and have long since lost touch with the franchise.  I find many things to like about the game design, in particular how most actions you will take will effect your good/evil rating such that over time you are seen by others as either a good guy or a bad guy.  The map is interesting to explore, with lots of strange and menacing discoveries to make.  The AI seems pretty good.Unfortunately on my recent iMac running OS X 10.10, the game runs terribly, worse than any game I have ever tried to play on this machine.  It goes without saying that I am forced under such circumstances to turn the graphics quality all the way down (which leaves the game looking like an early 90's game, and not in a charming retro way), but even with these measures taken, the game is either borderline unplayable or completely unplayable, depending on your patience.  (Mine wore out after about 15 hours of gameplay marred by stuttering frame rates, slow screen redraws, unresponsive buttons due to lag and so on.)Generally if I reboot the computer between sessions I can play for perhaps 20 minutes before the frame rate bogs down to the point of being unplayable.  I find that zooming out on the map causes the performance to plummet in such a way that it never recovers even after zooming back in to the normal perspective.Every time I exit the game I receive an error message that ""Age of Wonders III unexpectedly quit"", which is a good sign that all is not right with this build.With the issues I encountered I can't recommend this game to any Mac players whatsoever."
