76561197970571810,Recommended,226840,9862410,"Posted: 18 April, 2014",all,ExHippy,"A turn based strategy game in a similar vein to Fallen Enchantress. Game takes place on two levels, the overall strategic map, and a tactical battle map to resolve conflicts. Units come in quite a range of flavours from simple swordsmen up to and including what are basically tanks but the end game consists mainly of building large armies of whatever your single best unit is and throwing them at the enemy. You have a range of different different races with different base abilities but this only really impacts the early game as the special units (based on what class your leader is and researched into the middle of the game) tend to be massively better and are for the most part the same regardless of the race that built them.The AI isn't too much of a challenge on the strategic map, it does however do a decent job in the tactical battles.So all in all: not brilliant but certainly not bad. I got my money's worth out of it but I don't think I'll be replaying it anytime soon."
