76561198083624043,Not Recommended,226840,28134512,"Posted: 2 December, 2016",all,Bullwinkle,"A Review For Older Gamers: This is a good game, After 26 hours, I haven't seen any bugs, play is smooth, and there is great depth, well sort of.After playing for 5 hours, it is easy to get bored. You load up a new battle instance (yes - instance), place your units and move this unit, cast a spell with that, shoot with this one, click next turn. After a few turns the battle is over. Now it is time to move your units around the big map, make a quick empire-building move (maybe tell your city what to build next) and BACK TO BATTLE. That's all this game is: over and over, the same freaking battlefield instance with a few slightly different skins. Oooh! This time the battlefield instance has palm trees blocking the way instead of pillars of rock! Oooh!After 12 hours, you see there is a bit more to this game. Leveling up hero units, planning where to build cities on the big map, some exploration. After 25 hours, it becomes apparent that the decent amount of depth to the game barely matters. It is all elves and halflings and necromancers and eagle mounts and spider mounts and cities with walls that you break with trebuchets. It has been done so many times before, that even though they do a good job, it is just boring. The tired old tropes of spell casters and healers and warlords, mana potions and fairies and wisps and goblins...there is no WONDERMENT in Age of Wonders! It should be called Fellowship of the Ring, episode 293. And that includes having bought both DLC.When I  play ARK: Suvival Evolved, my jaw was constantly hanging open. Everywhere you turn, dinosaurs, fishing, sea diving, changing weather, stuff I had NOT done ten million times before. This game is the opposite of that, at least if you have read all the Tolkien books, seen all the movies, played all the games. Tired subject matter makes for a boring game. And the soundtrack is anything but exciting. The music never once lifts you up or tries to put you in a good mood. This is THINKING music. Furrow-your-brow, get a headache from thinking too hard for hours on end kind of music. Bleh! BORING!It is a polished, fun game, and even I will probably enjoy 100 or 200 hours in it, but only as a break from other games with more staying power. This game tries to be Medieval Civilization. To its credit, it is as well-polished as CIV, but it is too one-dimensional. Very little time is spent building the empire. Partly because they didn't build the tools you need to manage your empire. No over-riding view of research window where you can hang out and plan ahead, strategize. The in-game help is a little weak. Most of your time is in cookie-cutter *instanced* combat, which is fine, but deciding yet again how to flank a dragon and draw him out of volvanic lands into the fertile grassland your elven cavalry and druid prefer is just so totally yesterday, that even though this is a good game, I just can't bring myself to recommend it. Except on deep discount with no expectation of staying power. If you're going to remake Dungeons & Dragons One. More. Time., you should build the hell out of the game. Make it so you can rename your heros or at least enter notes so you can tell at a glance ""oh yeah, this is my dude with high fire resistance."" If you're not going to customize each heros character data sheet, at least ORGANIZE it so the important stuff is easy to find! The unit's ability to WALK isn't that interesting to me. Could you maybe not put that at the top? Let me click that slider bar and drag down til I find... oh there it is... no, this hero  can't buff his squad with extra damage... where is the dude who can? If this were 5 years ago, I'd say buy it. Today, this is just boring. Like your third replay of the entire Breaking Bad series on Netflix. Don't do it!Married people cheat on their spouse because they get bored and want something new. In the real world, there are reasons that gets complicated. In the fantasy world however, the excitement of getting some strange should be easy. Why isn't it? This game is good.... good in the way that sex with your wife of 22 years is also good. Yawn!! That was great! ...again. Yawn!! I'm sorry honey. But I know you understand. We've been married so long, you understood ten years ago. Want to watch some t.v.?"
