,Not Recommended,226840,10853925,"Posted: 26 June, 2014",all,alphagold3,"There are a lot of good games in this genre. Unfortunately, this isn't one of them. It is boring and simplistic compared to many others in the genre. It is trying to be a cross between a Civ game and something like the King's Bounty games or Heroes of Might and Magic and the crossover just ends up being the most mediocre of both worlds.For example, research consists of picking one of 12 seemingly random choices of spells or empire upgrades. There is no clear progression of research, it's just picking whichever random ability you want to research and most of them don't have a noticeably huge impact. Even worse than the annoying research system is the city development system. Your options for developing your cities are almost identical, no matter what race you are playing as. Every race gets 1 archer, 1 infantry unit, 1 irregular, 1 pikeman, 1 calvary unit, 1 siege tower, 1 support unit, and 1 special racial troop. The only differences between them for the different races are the traits they have and those don't have a huge difference. The class you choose for your hero has a bigger effect on what units you can build than your race but even that isn't much. No matter what class you pick, it adds 3 new building options to your city that must be built in order. Those buildings are what allow you to produce your class specific units. For the magical classes, that may be only 1 unit because you can use spells to summon more. For the non-magical classes, you get a few more troops but ultimately it is still an unsatisfying number of choices.The one thing I do like about this game is that if multiple armies are in hexes next to the army being attacked, you can have more troops in combat than a single army can have in it. However, combat still feels like a rather boring clone of King's Bounty or Heroes of Might and Magic's combat system. I'm not saying that those games are bad, just that this doesn't bring anything new to the combat table.All in all, I wouldn't recommend this game at all. You want to manage an empire, there are better games for that. You want to have turn based roleplaying game with tactical combat, there are better games for that. If you want to play both in the same game, then unfortunately this is the only game I know of for you but that doesn't means it's a good choice."
