76561198013729576,Recommended,226840,10881878,"Posted: 27 June, 2014",all,Roger Wilco,"To keep this to the point, the game is in a word, amazing.Part One: **Am I going to like this? / Should I get it?**Mechanics are tight, visuals are breathtaking, and the music is astounding. Skills and units are impressive for just about any playstyle. Enjoy rank and file common soldiers? It's Covered. Enjoy specilized troops to wreak havoc on the field? Have all you can enjoy! Researchable skills are also very easy to understand and have clear cut descriptions. I fully recommend this game!Part Two: **Learning Curve, Single Player, and Customization**This game is very easily picked up after a few minutes of in-game time. If anything is unclear there is a very in depth (and in game) manual with a nice search feature. Having just scratched the surface of the singleplayer game I can say thus far the story is rich and entertaining, any fantasy fan should be able to dive right in. Also, a very in-depth character creator for those of us who enjoy making our own fun! Now there isn't any unit customization, but honestly, I find that features like this only serve to bog a game down.Part Three: **""I NEED HELP!"" & Community**If you do happen to discover a problem with your game the devs are right there on the forums to assist you, there is also a very active community. Thus far as I've read on the forum's there are alot of people out there willing to help and to have some in-game fun with!Part Four: **The fanboy conclusion**I hate to sound like such a fan boy but honestly I've yet to discover something I dislike about this title, and look forward to sinking many more hours into Age of WOnders III !"
