76561198051862721,Recommended,226840,11119697,"Posted: 7 July, 2014",all,Loupuggg,"Having spent a considerable amount of time playing Civ5, I found Age of Wonders to be both familiar and fresh.  It's a tile-based unit moving city builder / war wager.  With my experience in this gaming genre I was playing within minutes of the download and I easily picked up the mechanics of the game during my first random map.  AoW3 is Civ5 in a fantasy setting, with added elements of role-playing that satisfies my other gaming addictions.  Orcs, elves, dragons, and other beasties are your playthings.  You can create a leader for your army, and pick up loot from your defeated foes to help your various stats.  AoW3 delves deeper than Civ5 in comabt, as you have the option to manually fight the battles rather than letting it auto-play out on your map.  I think the graphics are beautiful and the characters, created and stock, look great too.  With so much to do, including campaign mode and scenarios, not to mention online play, it will be easy to get that hours played number up to the hundreds."
