76561198230737444,Recommended,226840,17416526,"Posted: 6 August, 2015",all,Hanjin Hanamura,"I can say, without a doubt, that this game is worth buying for dedicated strategy players.If you make a massive session, eight players on a very large map, you had better be ready to spend DAYS on one world state. All of the races have their own unique troops, as does each class, but the real fun comes from blending those two factors to make the strongest army possible.Combat truely feels like it is betwen armies, whith surrounding units getting involved in the battle if they are afiliated with either side. There can be a total of 7 groups fighting in any battle, with each group containing up to 6 units, for up to 42 units being used in major, frequently player-versus-player battles.There is an auto-combat option, but with startegic thinking, you can turn a ""very Likely Defeat"" into victory by using spells and combat tactics against the various units- your own mind is your greatet weapon, as it SHOULD be in a strategy game.There are dungeons containing resources and trasure for you to find and raid, and there are unique structures you can only build when conquered dungeons are in a city's ""area of influence.""Random NPC cities can pop up, allowing you to be a conquerer or a uniter, combining other races into your army to make a dirverse fighting force. Some of thse cities have races that are not usually usable by the player. For example, there can be cities of trolls and giants, and you can use those races after conquering those cities.If you want a political map or something for a background, if you zoom out enough a map marking the enviroment and the various cities in your known area will appear in the style of a fanstasy paper map.You can create custom heroes by combining the previously mentioned races and classes with various skill affinites, such a using Creation magic or being an Explorer to create your own unique hero and thus a unique civilization for your army.All in all, this game is perfect for dedicated stategy fans, but sessions can take DAYS to complete, and the random, unafiliated units can be your downfall if you ignore them for too long."
