76561197971450461,Recommended,226840,16306093,"Posted: 11 June, 2015",all,Leto Tha Sec0nd,"From all the turn based fantasy games I always found the Age of Wonders series the best by far. The mixture of races and their units that you could force to work together appealed to me greatly. Age of Wonders III is the long awaited 4th game in the series and Triumph Studios did it again.In this iteration you can not only choose your race and spheres but you can now also pick a class. The class is what defines your style of play. They are very diverse and very well implemented into the game.Races are no longer inherent good, evil or neutral, neither are leaders. This all got replaces with the new happiness system, which influences not only moral but also city growth, city income, chance to crit or fumble in combat, etc... Happiness is crucial, it is a neat replacement for the removed mechanics that the original Age of Wonders series had.This game especially shines when playing a random map. There so many options to influence how you want to play and approach a map that I don't even know where to start.If there was only one game I could take with me on a spaceship to Mars, this would be it.I recommend getting every DLC, they are absolutely worth it, they only improve the base game and are packed with content."
