,Recommended,226840,27947101,"Posted: 28 November, 2016",all,Stupendous Man,"I've played Age of Wonders III for almost 100 hours as of writing this review, and I love the game. At first I couldn't really get into it; I started playing the first campaign which went well until the second mission, when the difficulty got much higher. I later came back to the game playing random maps, which taught me how to really play it.Now that I'm much more comfortable with the game, it's one of my favourite games. It has an excellent blend of strategy with tactical battles, and lots of different units to play with. This is both its strength and weakness though, as it takes a long time to get a feel for the different units and races.Now that I've become more proficient with the game, I'm really enjoying the campaigns which have a lot of story and world buidling. Also, the game has excellent music and a lot of charm. The world really feels alive and nuanced.While as of this writing there are 2 big DLCs for the game, the vanilla game has loads of content of its own. I didn't even buy the DLCs until recently as there was still so much to do in the base game. So if you just want to try the game without having to pay too much, buy the base game, You can then later add the 2 DLCs if you want more content.All in all, Age of Wonders III is a high quality game that is well worth the asking price, and a bargain on sale."
