76561197997760285,Recommended,226840,27093242,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,Endovior,"There've been a lot of 4x games out lately, including a lot of fantasy titles competing for the mantle of the ancient but much revered Master of Magic. Most of the recent ones fail miserably to live up to that legacy, and are at-best ok, or just sort of mediocre. The Age of Wonders series was pretty good, back in the day, but when I first played Age of Wonders III, shortly after release, I found it too slow and buggy to be worth my time. I gave it another try recently, thanks to a sale, and I've quite enjoyed my time with it, so far; it's the same Age of Wonders experience I enjoyed back in the day, but updated with more modern technology, including very pretty graphics.The game doesn't innovate much beyond the formula of previous titles in the series, but if you enjoyed the old Age of Wonders games, this latest edition is well worth your time and money. Especially if you buy it on sale!"
