76561198047898856,Recommended,226840,26420809,"Posted: 4 November, 2016",all,Jab 👌,"Amazing game, with all the DLC this is easily worth it on sale. The soundtrack is immersive, the graphics and environments are nice, and the game feels like it has a solid amount of depth with lots of replayability.I'm not sure if it's fair to call this game a ""4X title"", mainly because it's much more combat heavy which I've really enjoyed so far. It almost turns into a full out turn-based strategy/tactical RPG and I find it keeps things a lot more interesting. The city building isn't quite as in depth as a Civilization game for example, but I really enjoy exploring the map with my hero class, picking up items, leveling up and building up my army and cities as I go.Basically, I love all the Civilization games but they have really weak combat systems, this game however has a much better and enjoyable combat system so if you're after that in a 4X style game, I would highly recommend this.Also, the DLC are more like full out expansions.. the kind you got back in the late 90s and early 2000s, particularly the ""Eternal Lords"" one. I can see why people would have been disappointed to the lack of content in this game when it released, but it's come a long way and I think it's easily worth its price if you see it on sale."
