76561198086457357,Recommended,226840,15911837,"Posted: 20 May, 2015",all,Jelogisa,"==== TL;DR section ====Excellent 4X game, incredibly addictiveExploration: Good 9/10City Management : Simple 7/10Empire economics (resource gathering, building/manufacturing) : Excellent 9/10Tactical combat : Excellent 9/10Diplomacy: Simple 7/10Strategy: Good 8/10Graphics/Art: Excellent 9/10Gameplay/UI/Ease of use: Excellent 9/10World Design (Races/Classes/Terrains/...): Good 8/10Overall: Excellent 9/10=======================The game is not very complex in every of its aspect, but there are many aspects to consider, lots of things you can influence (and yet these facets are very well bundled up together, the game has a strong sense of purpose and unity). Well-done.It takes 2-5 hours to get a feeling of what you're doing at the beginning, then you get an incredibly addictive game with exploration, empire management, production/manufacturing, tactical combat, etc... . Once you get the hang of it, the syndrome 'just another turn' sets in (multiplied by a few hundred turns... and I'm likely to suffer from sleep deprivation for some time...)The universe is colorful and well designed. The gameplay is intense: while you solve a thorny problem, you're more than likely to get a handful of other problems and opportunities (make your choices, enjoy/suffer the consequences)...  There is always necessity for action and opportunities all around. You just have to pick a strategy and stick to it to progress in the game."
