76561198118312217,Recommended,226840,34669949,Posted: 1 September,all,Defenestrator,"AoW3 quickly turned into my favorite turn-based strategy game. The tactical battles are amazing, thanks to an abundance of unit skills and specialties that you can use. How efficiently you use your units has an enormous effect on how costly battles are for you, even when one opponent has an edge over the other. Sometimes, you will win against tough enemies with only minimal damage to your own units, because you were able to outmaneuver them, flank them for increased damage, and only allow them to attack your armored units that that you put in defensive mode.The AI seems pretty competent, sometimes making dumb moves, but also giving you a run for your money from time to time.But what I really love about this game is how the combination of race and class of your leader allows you to experiment with tons of possibilities for specialized units, and find amazing synergies.A nice detail is that instead of a simple team color, you choose a ""base color"" and a ""highlight color"" for your units. Pretty simple, but it looks awesome and gives you a ""This is my army!"" feeling.Another plus for me is that there are quite some mods available on the workshop, including tweaking and balancing mods as well as new content.Also: *Goblin Succubi*. Who can say no to a game that gives you Goblin Succubi?"
